<div id="review_1982695706" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1982695706" />
    <a title="Anthony" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/57796270-anthony"><img alt="Anthony" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1493991101p2/57796270.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1982695706?book_show_action=true">May 12, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Anthony" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Anthony" href="/user/show/57796270-anthony">Anthony</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Hardcover 9780892967049" href="/book/show/2033745.The_Bottoms">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1982695706" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer12866722132252256105">That was a great read, however sad and disturbing it be. Joe R Lansdale knows the perfect way to tell a tale, short and sweet, but packs a punch full of emotions. His style of writing is very easy going, like he&apos;s sitting at a campfire or just shooting the shit out on a hike and you&apos;re listening to him fully as to pass the time. He&apos;s got a good sense of humor, even for times where it wasn&apos;t meant to be funny... <br/><br/>And his language is authentic, the scenes come to life and everything seems beautiful</span>
  <span id="freeText12866722132252256105" style="display:none">That was a great read, however sad and disturbing it be. Joe R Lansdale knows the perfect way to tell a tale, short and sweet, but packs a punch full of emotions. His style of writing is very easy going, like he's sitting at a campfire or just shooting the shit out on a hike and you're listening to him fully as to pass the time. He's got a good sense of humor, even for times where it wasn't meant to be funny... <br /><br />And his language is authentic, the scenes come to life and everything seems beautiful and disturbingly real. I've only read three of his books now, and they all have that same rustic vibe. <br /><br /> Perfect reads for anyone who enjoys history and horror, and all that deep south goodness!</span>
  <a data-text-id="12866722132252256105" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


