<div id="review_2414089592" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2414089592" />
    <a title="Cody | CodysBookshelf" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/56352820-cody-codysbookshelf"><img alt="Cody | CodysBookshelf" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1626597053p2/56352820.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2414089592?book_show_action=true">Aug 06, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Cody | CodysBookshelf" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Cody | CodysBookshelf" href="/user/show/56352820-cody-codysbookshelf">Cody | CodysBookshelf</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Hardcover 9780892967049" href="/book/show/2033745.The_Bottoms">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/56352820-cody-codysbookshelf?shelf=favorites">favorites</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/56352820-cody-codysbookshelf?shelf=joe-r-lansdale">joe-r-lansdale</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2414089592" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer11160077964217334997">Damn it, Joe Lansdale, you broke my heart. Again.<br/><br/><i>The Bottoms</i> is one of this author’s more critically acclaimed novels, and rightfully so. It’s an involving and impeccably told mystery set in East Texas in 1933 — so, yes, this novel is right in Lansdale’s wheelhouse. Depression-era stories are what the Mojo Storyteller does best, and this is a corker.<br/><br/>Told in the first-person perspective of an old man looking back on his youth, this is about a series of murders going on in a small southern town — </span>
  <span id="freeText11160077964217334997" style="display:none">Damn it, Joe Lansdale, you broke my heart. Again.<br /><br /><i>The Bottoms</i> is one of this author’s more critically acclaimed novels, and rightfully so. It’s an involving and impeccably told mystery set in East Texas in 1933 — so, yes, this novel is right in Lansdale’s wheelhouse. Depression-era stories are what the Mojo Storyteller does best, and this is a corker.<br /><br />Told in the first-person perspective of an old man looking back on his youth, this is about a series of murders going on in a small southern town — and the boy’s father, the Constable, tries piecing things together. Told in Lansdale’s assured, country-fried style, this is a satisfying and enthralling yarn filled with easily likable characters and a strong sense of location.<br /><br />I debated taking off points for figuring out the mystery halfway through, but I still had fun — despite my sneaking suspicions. <i>The Bottoms</i> is more about the journey than the destination, anyway. A blurb calls this an “R-rated version of <i>The Andy Griffith Show</i>,” and . . . yeah, that about hits the nail on the head. Highly recommended! </span>
  <a data-text-id="11160077964217334997" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

