  <span id="freeText14450758188267539484" style="display:none">Not so much of a whodunit as an i-know-whodunit. The identities of the murderer and Goat Man were clear to me by page 200. I much preferred Landale's Sunset and Sawdust, which gripped from the first page to the last. Still, Lansdale's incapable of writing bad literature, and for this reason it's four stars. It’s also highly recommended :)</span>
